    "Basically, Clarivate applies an algorithm to cluster highly cited papers by authors followed by a cleaning process based on visual inspection.",
    "According to Szomszor et al. (2020) \"the publication clusters associated with Highly Cited Researchers have a high level of manual curation\" (p. 1125).",
    "The non-transparent cleaning process leaves room for speculation on the exclusion of certain researchers from the list of HCRs.",
    "While criteria like scientific 1 Clarivate changed the methodology in 2022, but did not report HCRs lists based on the changed methodology retrospectively.",
    "Therefore it is not possible to directly assess the effect of the methodology change on the lists."
